content:
Correctness_Score: 0.7
Style_Score: 0.6
Simplicity_Score: 0.5
Robustness_Score: 0.5
Reasoning: The provided solution is functionally correct on the sample inputs and on many randomized small tests I executed (sample tests and ~200 randomized cases passed). However, it does not use small-to-large (merge-by-size) optimization when merging color dictionaries, so its worst-case time complexity can be quadratic and will likely TLE on adversarial large inputs under the problem constraints; this is why Correctness is reduced. Style is modest: there are brief helpful comments and clear variable names but minimal documentation. Simplicity is average because the code is concise and easy to follow but misses the key efficiency trick; robustness is likewise middling since edge cases (empty boxes) are handled but the approach is not scalable or optimal for large inputs.
